A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing January 27, 2025, as International Holocaust Remembrance Day; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Holocaust was the state-sponsored, systematic persecution and annihilation
4 of European Jews by Nazi Germany and its collaborators between 1933 and 1945, resulting
5 in the murder of six million Jews as well as the oppression and deaths of millions of others,
6 including Roma, people with disabilities, and Poles; and
7 WHEREAS, in 1998, HB 1664 was passed by the Georgia state legislature, establishing the
8 Georgia Commission on the Holocaust as a permanent state agency charged with creating
9 educational programs for Georgia citizens and operating as a secular, non-partisan entity; and
10 WHEREAS, the Georgia Commission on the Holocaust is tasked with preserving the
11 memory of the Holocaust, promoting public understanding of its history, and reminding
12 citizens to remain vigilant against hatred, racism, antisemitism, persecution, and genocide;
13 and
